public class LUCICabinetMap_Shard<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends LUCICabinetMap<K,V>

This class implements a sharded database. This means that key-value pairs are stored in a collection of different databases based on a function of their key. A sharded database speeds up concurrent access and enables scaling to large databases (in theory). Although the methods are synchronized to manage concurrent access to this object, the actual work of accessing the database is offloaded to a separate worker queue per shard so that methods should return quickly.

Constructor Detail

LUCICabinetMap_Shard

public LUCICabinetMap_Shard(java.util.List<LUCICabinetMap<K,V>> shards)
Parameters:
shards - A list of databases to shard across. If any of these databases are the same database, or are remote wrappers for the same database, then iterations will go across each copy of the database one time (effectively iterating more than once across entries) The sharding function is the default based on a modulo of the hash function.

LUCICabinetMap_Shard

Parameters:
shard - A list of databases to shard across. If any of these databases are the same database, or are remote wrappers for the same database, then iterations will go across each copy of the database one time (effectively iterating more than once across entries)
sf - An object which defines how to associate keys with shards.
